The following javascript, on ajax submit causes firefox to display an in-window blank dialog. Clicking OK or Cancel does not do anything. Application has to be killed and restarted. 

jQuery("#assetManagement").submit(function() {
      jQuery("[name='submit']").attr("disabled","disabled");
      jQuery(this).submit();
    //  return false; // just submitted.
  });

Reproducible: Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Attempt to submit page with the above code in it
2.
3.

Actual Results:  
Stops operating, appears to be waiting for input to dialog, but nothing.

Expected Results:  
Not to be crashed

